{"TopicId":178687,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Are kerbals\u0026#039; personal parachutes \u0026quot;automatic?\u0026quot;","CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T09:45:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T09:45:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I\u0027m doing a thing. And the thing is working pretty well... but not to the end I really wanted.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI built a craft which launches kerbals a huge distance while in command seats. The thing is basically a multi-kerbal cannon.\u003Cbr\u003E\nTrouble is, every time I stage the cannon... all 8 kerbals deploy their personal parachutes and I don\u0027t understand why.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n*I have not armed their personal \u0027chutes at any time during the boarding process.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*I have not pressed \u0022P,\u0022 which I understand to be the default button to arm the \u0027chutes.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*I have not found any possible way to intentionally stage\u00A0kerbals\u0027 personal \u0027chutes.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*On activating the cannon, I only need to stage; no other keys are pressed.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*Control focus is always on the cannon, even though I aim the camera in the right-click menu at the \u0022cannonball\u0022 kerbals.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*This save is an unmodded sandbox game (with the exception of Kerbal Engineer Redux)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAre kerbals\u0027 personal \u0027chutes automatically armed to deploy\u00A0in a freefall scenario when your control point is not on them, or have I found a bug?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-02T12:21:26Z\u0022 title=\u002210/02/2018 12:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 2, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Dark Lion\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T09:50:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe. Can you check that you did not switch the parachute deployment button to spacebar?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T11:58:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166634-dark-lion/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022166634\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/166634-dark-lion/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dark Lion\u003C/a\u003EIt\u0027s not a bug, it\u0027s a feature.\u00A0When you put Kerbals in command seats, their \u0027chutes become part of the staging sequence of that vessel. I\u0027m not sure if there\u0027s any way to disable this, but make sure the Kerbals\u0027 parachutes (they should be a parachute icon in the staging sequence)\u00A0are in a stage\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eafter\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0the one that activates your cannon. Don\u0027t have them enable before or at the same time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-02T12:00:19Z\u0022 title=\u002210/02/2018 12:00  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 2, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by RealKerbal3x\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T12:05:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188222-xd-the-great/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188222\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188222-xd-the-great/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Xd the great\u003C/a\u003E I would never do that.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027m savvy with setting up my controls, as I like to switch roll and yaw controls, as well as use H and N for rovers\u0027 forward and reverse, respectively. I change \u003Cem\u003Eno other\u003C/em\u003E key bindings but those.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183830-realkerbal3x/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022183830\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183830-realkerbal3x/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealKerbal3x\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0you might be onto something there. Either I wasn\u0027t paying attention to whether or not things were being added to my staging, or nothing was... I\u0027ll get back to you in a few minutes to verify.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183830-realkerbal3x/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022183830\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183830-realkerbal3x/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealKerbal3x\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I\u0027m afraid it\u0027s not\u00A0as you suggest.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/V8F3OQo.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022V8F3OQo.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs you can see here, there\u0027s nothing new being added to the staging sequence for me to manipulate...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T12:18:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same, frustrating result:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/EBts7pS.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022EBts7pS.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dark Lion","CreatedById":166634,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T22:26:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223460919\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538473839\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188222\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xd the great\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Xd the great said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe. Can you check that you did not switch the parachute deployment button to spacebar?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI apologize for my previous pessimistic outlook \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188222-xd-the-great/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188222\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/188222-xd-the-great/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Xd the great\u003C/a\u003E... Here\u0027s a snap of my key-bindings.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/F7eT77T.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022F7eT77T.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn the interest of being fair and getting to the bottom of this, I\u0027ll be more open to suggestion henceforth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xd the great","CreatedById":188222,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-02T23:24:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ips